SIMPLE: admeasure
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Admeasure
<hw>Ad*meas"ure</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>amesurer</ets>, LL. <ets>admensurare</ets>. See
<er>Measure</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To measure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>To determine the proper share of,
or the proper apportionment; <as>as, to <ex>admeasure</ex> dower; to
<ex>admeasure</ex> common of pasture.</as></def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The measure of a thing; dimensions; size.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Formerly, the adjustment of
proportion, or ascertainment of shares, as of dower or pasture held in
common. This was by writ of <xex>admeasurement</xex>, directed to the
sheriff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Admeasurer</ent>⟦br⟧
